items.title: Anthropic's Claude Code can now read your Slack messages and write code for you
items.summary: Anthropic launches Slack integration that lets software engineers delegate coding tasks without leaving Slack . Anthropic's Claude Code has emerged as a surprise revenue engine, generating over $1 billion in annualized revenue just six months after its public debut in May . The Slack integration arrives at a pivotal moment for Anthropic, which continues to barrel toward scale with Netflix, Spotify, and Salesforce .

items.title: Booking.com’s agent strategy: Disciplined, modular and already delivering 2× accuracy
items.summary: Booking.com has seen accuracy double across key retrieval, ranking and customer-interaction tasks . Pranav Pathak: "The better we are at customer service, the more loyal our customers are" The company is taking a disciplined, layered, modular approach to model development: small, travel-specific models for cheap, fast inference and larger large language models .

items.title: Design in the age of AI: How small businesses are building big brands faster
items.summary: Since 2022, global interest in “AI business name generator” has surged more than 700% . Small businesses aren’t waiting for enterprise AI to trickle-down, they’re adopting these tools en masse . Tools like Design.com merge naming, logo creation, and website generation into a single workflow . The five frontiers of AI-powered entrepreneurship mirror the creative journey every founder takes .

items.title: Why AI coding agents aren’t production-ready: Brittle context windows, broken refactors, missing operational awareness
items.summary: This article will examine the practical pitfalls and limitations observed when engineers use modern coding agents for real enterprise work . AI agents struggle significantly with designing scalable systems due to the sheer explosion of choices and a critical lack of enterprise-specific context . Large enterprise codebases and monorepos are often too vast for agents to directly learn from, and crucial knowledge can be frequently fragmented across internal documentation and individual expertise .
